<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM2.7.8">
<l>alaṅkeḻu taṭakkai yāyaṉvā yāmpaṟ kaḻiyumā leṉṉuḷḷa meṉṉum</l>
<l>pulaṅkeḻu porunīrp puṭkuḻi pāṭum pōtumō nīrmalaik keṉṉum</l>
<l>kulaṅkeḻu kolli kōmaḷa vallik koṭiyiṭai neṭumaḻaik kaṇṇi</l>
<l>yilaṅkeḻil tōḷik keṉṉiṉain tiruntā yiṭaventai yentaipi rāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>“My heart will surely melt for the flute at the mouth of the herder</l>
<l rend="indent">in whose broad, bright hand is the plough,” she says.</l>
<l>She sings of Puṭkuḻi where bright waters crash in fields;</l>
<l rend="indent">she says, “Shall we go to Nīrmalai?”</l>
<l>What were you intending, lord father of Iṭaventai, for this tender creeper</l>
<l rend="indent">of lovely, bright Kolli [Hill],</l>
<l>The one with shining, graceful arms, long dewy eyes, and vine[-like] waist?</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
